dules, managing patient waiting lists, rescheduling patients, and making adjustments to clinician schedules. This role requires attention to detail and experience in digital healthcare scheduling.',5740,1743,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(665,'Senior Full Stack Developer - Data Science Applications (Remote, US)','As a Fullstack Software Engineer at Collective[i], you will support the Data Science team by designing, developing, and maintaining web applications. Responsibilities include developing scalable applications, designing RESTful APIs, collaborating with teams, participating in code reviews, and optimizing performance.',5788,397,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,100000.00,150000.00,0),(666,'Senior Systems Analyst','The Senior Systems Analyst will analyze business and technical processes, document system flows, and reverse-engineer applications. They will collaborate with various teams to assess systems and implement technological advancements in Asset Management, focusing on delivering high-quality software and utilizing Agile practices.',2652,390,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(667,'Data Engineer','The Data Engineer will design, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines and infrastructure to support data-intensive applications and analytics. Responsibilities include collaborating with data scientists, implementing ETL processes, optimizing data models, and deploying solutions on cloud platforms while ensuring data quality and governance.',5085,475,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(668,'Coding Expertise for AI Training - Tier 2 - US','The role involves helping train generative AI models by crafting and answering computer science questions and evaluating AI-generated code. It\'s a remote freelance position requiring coding expertise and attention to detail.',5930,1845,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(669,'Head Partner Director - Channel Sales / Engagement Management Sales','The Head Partner Director leads and inspires the Partner Director team, Engagement Manager team, and Recruiter sales teams to drive growth through new and established partnerships. Responsibilities include overseeing sales teams, setting quotas, maintaining strong partner relationships, and collaborating with various departments to achieve sales and revenue goals.',5399,1591,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(670,'Principal Account Management Support','The GDS Account Manager supports day-to-day technical needs for airline customers in the US and Canada, serving as a contact for escalations. Responsibilities include product enhancements, implementation coordination, collaboration with account directors, resolving critical issues, identifying solutions, and generating new business opportunities while maintaining strong customer relationships.',4370,865,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(671,'Billing Specialist','The Billing Specialist is responsible for managing client billing inquiries, processing credit and debit memos, creating invoices, and analyzing sales contracts. This role includes collaborating with various departments, conducting audits, and improving billing processes.',1805,443,8,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(672,'Director of Revenue Accounting','The Director of Revenue Accounting will lead the revenue recognition processes, ensuring compliance with accounting standards like ASC 606. This role involves developing the revenue accounting function, collaborating with cross-functional teams, and providing strategic insights. The candidate will drive process improvements and enhancements, coordinate with auditors, and deliver revenue reporting to support management decisions.',5266,447,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(673,'Staff Analytics Engineer','As a Staff Analytics Engineer, you will design and build data pipelines and infrastructure to enhance operational performance. Collaborating with data scientists and engineers, you\'ll ensure clean, accessible data and contribute to data strategy focusing on quality and governance. Mentor junior team members and optimize data systems for business operations.',1706,390,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,145000.00,171000.00,0),(674,'Technical Lead (Salesforce)','The Technical Lead (Salesforce) at Thunder is responsible for overseeing Salesforce implementations, developing custom solutions, providing technical guidance, resolving issues, and collaborating with different teams. This role also involves project planning, documentation, and continuous improvement initiatives while managing offshore resources and training users.',5800,447,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(675,'Email Marketing Associate','The Email Marketing Associate will develop and deploy email strategies for nonprofits, manage email lists, perform QA testing, analyze performance data, and collaborate with teams to maximize campaign effectiveness. The role requires a blend of digital marketing skills, particularly in email marketing with knowledge in HTML/CSS.',5057,1174,7,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0);
